        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"><img src=icon_smile_question.gif border=0 align=middle><BR>OK, Here goes (My first post here.)</P><P>I am level 14 (My highest is level 39, a Wizard, so I'm not all that new to Int Casters).</P><P>I'm also a Dark Elf.  I chose Dark Elf because of the look and feel, as well as the starting stats and hometown faction.  But recently, I've become worried, and unsure if (Question #1) I should restart as an Iksar...?  Is the difference really that large...?</P><P>Typicaly, I've been soloing crocodiles and caimans (and occasionaly a Deepwater Caiman) in Oasis, the going seems sort of slow, so I tend to group some...</P><P>A typical fight generally goes a little something like pull with darkness, let pet tank while I fear.  DoT the MoB with a low DoT (If it's red, or high yellow I tend to stack a DoT or two more), and then melee while keeping it feared.  However I can average 1 or sometimes 2 kills per Full Mana.  It seems from my friends, that I should have more mana than this (I have plenty of INT Gear, especially for my level although I'm hardly any supertwink, my main is fairly poor).</P><P>When I'm grouped, I don't feel like I use my abilities to the best, I'm generally not allowed to Snare or Fear, and things drop so quickly that my DoTs are almost a waste. Because of this, I tend to avoid grouping.</P><P>So, in short... (Question #2) Is there anything I should make sure I'm doing, is there anything I should do differently?</P><P>Also, (Question #3) Anyone tips on where to hunt BESIDES Oasis at my level, and in the levels to come?</P><P>One of the main reasons I don't play my Wizard as much is because of things like having a Wandering Blue con in Eastern Wastes bop me a few times and leave me dead in 2 seconds, the mana inefficiency of my soloing, and my lack of group appeal.</P><P>I feel I know what Necros are supposed to be (I'm not looking to be sought after for raids, or looking to be an essential member for groups)...</P><P>If this all comes out as a bunch of incoherent drivel, it's because my mind jumps all over the place when I post, and I think I communicated my idea well, but I didn't.</P><P>"The only thing we know for sure is that we don't know anything for sure"</font></td>
