        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=50844&TOPIC_ID=6407&FORUM_ID=11&CAT_ID=5&Forum_Title=Newbie+Hall&Topic_Title=New+Necromancer%3A+Questions+about+fighting+and+Mana&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>


        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">first off - don't melee :) Ever :)</P><P>Past level 12 or so there is little point in meleeing - when soloing, just keep fear and darkness on with a couple of dots and let pet do the tanking.  You med up and recast fear, dark etc as appropriate.</P><P>Use allure and lifetap when you need to regain some hp. </P><P>Grouping is tough. For dots I'd say use the poison based ones as they are fast enough not to be wasted in groups (ya, I know the level 4 one is poxy.) Also good is the disease line. Just be careful to make sure mob has been tanked a bit first before you do start dotting - especially when using debuff dots like heart flutter at level 16.</P><P>A good mob to kill in your teens is Jonah in Lake Rathe. Combine this with blacksmithing (he drops lots and lots of water...). Otherwise, zones which are good to fight in are the traditional ones everyone mentions.</P><P>Personally, I can see the attraction of iksar regen at lower levels. But it really does count for diddly squat in the higher levels. More of an advantage is their higher ac but again, at higher levels, if a mob is hitting you it's time to fd or head for zone...</P><P>Regards,</P><P>Felly</P><P><BR>Felinaval Dreamweaver<BR>52 Heretic<BR>Mystic Valor<BR>Saryrn Server</P><P>"For in the end we all shall die. Until then let me seek glory!"<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
